"{\n  \"text\": \"Hey everybody, Scotty here. Plants get their nutrients from microbes and fungus within the soil. Living soil will literally sequester all the life that it needs, all the minerals and vitamins and uh nutrients that needs and deliver it to the root structure. The roots then produce exudates, which these microbes and this fungus will live off of. It's a symbiotic exchange. Your gut works the exact same way. They deliver the nutrients that your body needs directly to it. You don't just get it from the food or the chemicals or the vitamins. You deliver it to the new to the microbes, and the microbes deliver it to you just as you need it. It's a very precise system, but you don't just get it directly from these vitamins. You have to feed your gut bacteria, and then in turn that gut bacteria feeds you. This is why you need to eat living foods such as raw fruits and vegetables and fermented foods, like Scotty's fermented foods available at ScottysFoods.com. Thanks, y'all.\",\n  \"sentences\": [\n    {\n      \"text\": \" Hey everybody, Scotty here.\",\n      \"start\": 0.32,\n      \"end\": 2.24,\n      \"duration\": 1.92,\n      \"confidence\": 0.994,\n      \"tokens\": [\n        {\n          \"text\": \" He\",\n          \"start\": 0.32,\n          \"end\": 0.56,\n          \"duration\": 0.24,\n          \"confidence\": 0.993\n        },\n        {\n          \"text\": \"y\",\n          \"start\": 0.56,\n          \"end\": 0.72,\n          \"duration\": 0.16,\n          \"confidence\": 1.0\n        },\n        {\n          \"text\": \" ever\",\n          \"start\": 0.8,\n          \"end\": 0.88,\n          \"duration\": 0.08,\n          \"confidence\": 1.0\n        },\n        {\n          \"text\": \"yb\",\n          \"start\": 0.88,\n          \"end\": 1.04,\n          \"duration\": 0.16,\n          \"confidence\": 1.0\n        },\n        {\n          \"text\": \"ody\",\n          \"start\": 1.04,\n          \"end\": 1.12,\n          \"duration\": 0.